brand.description:
The company that this device is branded with.
Example: "Google", "Samsung"
@OutputOnly

codename.description:
The name of the industrial design.
This corresponds to android.os.Build.DEVICE
@OutputOnly

id.description:
The unique opaque id for this model.
Use this for invoking the TestExecutionService.
@OutputOnly

name.description:
The human-readable marketing name for this device model.
Examples: "Nexus 5", "Galaxy S5"
@OutputOnly

screenDensity.description:
Screen density in DPI.
This corresponds to ro.sf.lcd_density
@OutputOnly

apiLevel.description:
The API level for this Android version.
Examples: 18, 19
@OutputOnly

codeName.description:
The code name for this Android version.
Examples: "JellyBean", "KitKat"
@OutputOnly

id.description:
An opaque id for this Android version.
Use this id to invoke the TestExecutionService.
@OutputOnly

versionString.description:
A string representing this version of the Android OS.
Examples: "4.3", "4.4"
@OutputOnly

id.description:
The id for this locale.
Example: "en_US"
@OutputOnly

name.description:
A human-friendly name for this language/locale.
Example: "English"
@OutputOnly

id.description:
The id for this orientation.
Example: "portrait"
@OutputOnly

name.description:
A human-friendly name for this orientation.
Example: "portrait"
@OutputOnly

errorMessage.description:
If the TestState is ERROR, then this string will contain human-readable
details about the error.
@OutputOnly

invalidMatrixDetails.description:
Describes why the matrix is considered invalid.
Only useful for matrices in the INVALID state.
@OutputOnly
